===Etymology===
Contracted from '''[[God]] [[blind]] [[me]]!''' so as not to seem like [[blasphemy]];<!-- in [[medieval]] times, people would curse using [[contractions]] rather than breaking the [[w:Ten commandments|third commandment]] (Do not use the Lord's name in [[vain]] [[oath]]s).--> compare '''[['sblood]]''', '''[[strewth]]''', '''[[zounds]]''', etc.

===Interjection===
'''blimey!'''

#Formerly used as an oath and to express anger or wonder.
#Expressing [[surprise]].

